    "title": "GPU Memory Math for LLMs (2026 Edition)",
    "preview_text": "If you’re running models locally, thinking “model → VRAM” falls apart once you account for how the weights were trained and quantized in the first place.\nThere’s a better way to think about it:\nVRAM",
    "cover_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HE_mtS9XkAAaJlc.jpg",
    "content_state": {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ep8u",
          "text": "If you’re running models locally, thinking “model → VRAM” falls apart once you account for how the weights were trained and quantized in the first place.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "csl0q",
          "text": "There’s a better way to think about it:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 73,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "5hue1",
          "text": "VRAM (in GB) ≈ Parameters (in billions) x (effective bits per weight ÷ 8)",
          "type": "blockquote"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bomei",
          "text": "That’s it.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "cf90",
          "text": "This one formula explains everything across:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6qhc7",
          "text": "FP16 / BF16",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "dm65a",
          "text": "FP8 / INT8",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "mgi1",
          "text": "GPTQ / AWQ / NF4",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "eh7v2",
          "text": "GGUF variants",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "coigp",
          "text": "basically every format you’ll use",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "47qhf",
          "text": "The Only Conversion You Actually Need",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "4k4gu",
          "text": "Here’s the core intuition:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1fbak",
          "text": "FP16 / BF16 → 16 bits → ~2 GB per 1B params",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "5pga3",
          "text": "FP8 / INT8 → 8 bits → ~1 GB per 1B params",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "dc1f6",
          "text": "4-bit quants → ~4 bits → ~0.5 GB per 1B params",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "3ibp8",
          "text": "GGUF formats sit in between depending on the exact scheme:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "am9tq",
          "text": "Q6_K → ~0.82 GB per 1B",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "a9sln",
          "text": "Q5_K → ~0.69 GB per 1B",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "el80e",
          "text": "Q4_K → ~0.56 GB per 1B",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "al9li",
          "text": "Q3_K → ~0.43 GB per 1B",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "23bmg",
          "text": "Q2_K → ~0.33 GB per 1B",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "78hb",
          "text": "Ultra-aggressive quants go even lower, but at a cost.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "32tlu",
          "text": "If you remember nothing else, remember this:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ef34n",
          "text": "FP16 = 2x model size",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "aiu0r",
          "text": "FP8 = 1x model size",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "3sufg",
          "text": "4-bit = 0.5x model size",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ct7q0",
          "text": "Everything else is just variations on that theme.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "9s3f",
          "text": "Side Note: The VRAM Tax Nobody Talks About",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 0,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "f778o",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "8g6ke",
          "text": "Before you even think about weights, understand this: the model itself is only part of your VRAM bill. The real killer is everything around it. KV cache grows with context length and will quietly eat your memory alive at 32K, 128K, or higher. Activations vary by runtime and optimization level but can spike under certain execution paths. Batching and concurrency multiply memory usage fast, especially in agent-style workloads. Framework overhead adds its own tax depending on whether you’re using Transformers, vLLM, TensorRT-LLM, or llama.cpp. And then there’s CUDA Graphs, which trade extra reserved memory for much better latency and throughput stability. Bottom line: if you only budget for weights, you’re already out of memory.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "98d1c",
          "text": "What This Looks Like in Practice",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "802k9",
          "text": "Let’s translate that into real model sizes.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1vj07",
          "text": "A 7B model:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "avs7b",
          "text": "FP16 → ~14 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "fq0d6",
          "text": "FP8 → ~7 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "c54eb",
          "text": "4-bit → ~3.5–4 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1l2e1",
          "text": "A 13B model:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "e7q8t",
          "text": "FP16 → ~26 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1jims",
          "text": "FP8 → ~13 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6825i",
          "text": "4-bit → ~6–7 GB",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "4po15",
          "text": "A 70B model:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
